      <head>Lorle Meissner</head>
      <div>
        <p>German or Austrian singer.</p>

        <div>
          <head>Meissner and Schenker's Circle</head>
          <p>Daughter of Helene Vischer, Lorle Meissner was named in letters of August 1912 from
              <ref cRef="entity-000951">Hans Weisse</ref> to Schenker (<ref type="correspondence"
              cRef="OJ-15-15_I">OJ 15/15, [I]</ref> and <ref type="correspondence" cRef="OJ-15-16_8"
              >OJ 15/16, [8]</ref>) as wishing to sing <ref cRef="entity-000951">Hans Weisse</ref>'s
            song-set <title level="m">Mädchenlieder</title>. In July of that year (<ref
              type="correspondence" cRef="OJ-15-16_6">OJ 15/16, [6]</ref>) the well-known Dutch
            mezzo-soprano <ref cRef="entity-000145">Julia Culp</ref> had expressed the same
            willingness, and it may be that Schenker recommended Meissner after the Culp prospect
            had foundered.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
